/letgo.wasm

/scratch
/scratch/*
benchmark/letgo

.clj-kondo
.lsp
*.calva-repl
CLAUDE.md
.claude
.DS_Store
.nrepl-port

# Fennel benchmark dependencies
benchmark/fennel/lib/
benchmark/gloat/bin/
AGENTS.md

# Local goreleaser / cross-build artifacts
/dist/

# AOT codegen tool — built ad-hoc, not checked in
/lgbgen
/lginterop
/bench-ratchet

# bench-ratchet streams per-bench results here on capture; the
# aggregated baseline is in docs/perf/baseline.json (committed).
docs/perf/.runs/

# transient stash used by check-generated
pkg/rt/.core_compiled.lgb.committed

# gogen_ir AOT artifacts — build artifacts, NOT committed. Regenerated by
# `lgbgen --target=go` (via `make generate` / `make check-generated`). Their
# self-lower is wall-clock-nondeterministic, so committing them would churn;
# the untagged build and shipped bytecode binary never need them.
pkg/rt/generated.provenance
pkg/rt/core_go_lowered/
/lg_gogen_ir.go
/cmd/lgbgen/main_gogen_ir.go
/pkg/ir/zz_gogen_ir_wire_test.go
# Native-lowering trampoline (scripts/gogen-trampoline.lg) scratch: a transient
# //go:build lg_trampoline wireup written at the repo root while it builds a
# tagged binary. Cleaned up by the trampoline, but ignore any leftover from an
# aborted run. (The lowered package it emits lives under the already-ignored
# pkg/rt/core_go_lowered/.)
/zz_lg_trampoline_gen.go
.gold-clojure-version

# lean-ctx local tool state
.lean-ctx/
